  "informal_statement": "For all reals a, b, c, d: min a c + min b d <= min (a+b) (c+d) -- the minimum function is superadditive.",
  "informal_proof_idea": "By le_min, it suffices to show min a c + min b d is at most both a+b and c+d. The first follows from min_le_left a c (min a c <= a) and min_le_left b d (min b d <= b), summed via linarith; the second follows symmetrically from min_le_right on both pairs.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem min_add_min_le (a b c d : ℝ) : min a c + min b d ≤ min (a + b) (c + d)",
